title: AfterInteractedWithItems
position: 315,-648
---
<<fade_transition 2>>
<<wait 1>>
<<hide_all_objects>>
<<hide_ui ClickToInteract>>
<<show Stars>>
<<show Sitting>>
This is the life that I've committed myself to, ever since taking the job to pilot this small exploration vessel.
Earth launched an initiative to find out why the sun suddenly had a hole in the center... a dark spot that appeared one day and never went away. It's a three-year journey just to get there. I'm on the seventh expedition they've sent.
My dad was the pilot of the last one. He never returned.
But deep inside, I knew signing up was just to get a chance away from Earth.
You: I guess I have some time... what should I do?
    -> (contemplate my life on Earth)
        I ponder the vastness of existence and my place within it.
        The silence of space seems to amplify my thoughts, making me feel both insignificant and connected to the universe.
        -> (hone in on the positive)
            I think back to a time I felt connected with someone on Earth, recalling when my mother taught me how to bake cookies.
            She doesn't show much affection anymore. Not since Dad never came back from his expedition. Mostly distrust. But the memory still brings a smile to my face. 
            <<set $posSelfPerception += 1>>
            It's a small comfort in the loneliness of space. I feel <color=\#88FF88>slightly happier</color>.
        -> (dwell on the negative)
            I think back about a time I felt insignificant on Earth.
            Ever since I dropped out of college, I've felt like a disappointment to my family.
            I took the first contract that would launch me off-planet, telling myself distance would make it easier to breathe.
            <<set $negSelfPerception += 1>>
            I scoff at the concept of unconditional love. In doing so, I <color=\#FF8888>feel sadder</color>, overwhelmed by the vast emptiness around me.
    -> (think of something happy)
        I think back to my time on Earth, recalling when my mother taught me how to bake cookies.
        She doesn't show much affection anymore. Not since Dad never came back. Mostly distrust. But the memory still brings a smile to my face. 
        <<set $posSelfPerception += 1>>
        It's a small comfort in the loneliness of space. I feel <color=\#88FF88>slightly happier</color>.
    -> (do some push-ups)
        I was never huge on fitness, but I was required to keep in shape for space travel.
        My father never returned from the last expedition to the dark spot. Mom's still on Earth, but she never supported my leaving... only distrust, after losing him.
        Part of me still wants to prove that coming out here wasn't just another failure.
        <<set $posSelfPerception += 1>>
        I do a few push-ups to keep my strength up. Strangely enough, I feel <color=\#88FF88>a little happier</color> afterwards.
<<play_sound AlarmClock>>
A timer goes off in the background.
You: Sounds like it's time to do my report.
<<hide_all_objects>>
<<show PCRoom>>
<<jump DoJobFirstTime>>
