title: EnterMessage
position: 316,-234
---
I'm frozen in place. Is this really happening?
My mouth doesn't open. I can't speak a word. My voice... is gone.
Out of the hundreds of days I've spent in space, I've never seen something like this.
What should... I... do?
    -> (let the signal through)
        <<jump CatIntro>>
    -> (ignore the signal)
You: ..........
Against my better judgment, I decide to ignore the signal. 
You: Darn static interference...
<<set $negSelfPerception += 1>>
<<hide_all_characters>>
<<fade_transition 2>>
<<wait 1.5>>
<<play_sound Glitch 0.25>>
<<show_character Cat Obscure right>>
Suddenly, the same signal reappears on the screen. Whatever it is won't take ignorance for an answer.
    -> (let the signal through)
        <<jump CatIntro>>
    -> (unplug the monitor)
        <<hide_all_characters>>
        <<hide MonitorSilhouette>>
        I decide to unplug the monitor, cutting off the signal entirely.
        After a few moments, the screen flickers back to static. I'm alone, again.
        <<jump ForeverAloneNoContact>>
